    <h2>Honourable Mentions</h2>

    <p><strong>Skruf Super White</strong> — Swedish manufacturing, white pouch, tobacco-free. Premium quality at a step below Kelly White. Excellent for users who want Scandinavian pedigree without the highest premium.</p>

    <p><strong>FUMI</strong> — Turkish brand, 30 mg strength, strong competitor to Siberia. Slightly smoother flavour, fractionally cheaper. Fewer retailers stock it, but worth seeking out if extreme strength is your goal.</p>

    <p><strong>ACE</strong> — Scandinavian heritage, white pouches, subtle spice notes. Less widely available than ZYN or VELO, but loyal users swear by the flavour refinement.</p>

    <p><strong>XQS</strong> — Budget-friendly, wide strength range (1–18 mg), good all-rounder. Not a category winner, but solid if your local shop stocks it and price matters most.</p>

    <h2>How to Find Your Perfect Pouch</h2>

    <p><strong>Step 1: Choose Your Strength</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Beginner (first-time ever):</strong> 3–4 mg (VELO Simply Spearmint Mini)</li>
      <li><strong>Light daily use:</strong> 6–8 mg (ZYN Cool Mint Regular, LOOP Mint Mania)</li>
      <li><strong>Regular daily use:</strong> 10–13.5 mg (ZYN Menthol Ice Slim, VELO medium range)</li>
      <li><strong>Heavy daily use:</strong> 18+ mg (Siberia, FUMI, ZYN Slim S5)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Step 2: Pick Your Flavour Profile</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Mint lovers → ZYN Menthol Ice</li>
      <li>Flavour explorers → VELO range</li>
      <li>Traditionalists → Kelly White, Skruf</li>
      <li>Minimalists → ZYN Cool Mint</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Step 3: Consider Format</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Regular:</strong> Larger pouch, more saliva, longer release (90 mins+). Good for all-day sessions.</li>
      <li><strong>Slim:</strong> Smaller pouch, discreet, faster release (45–60 mins). Ideal for work or social settings.</li>
      <li><strong>Mini:</strong> Smallest format, fastest release. Perfect for new users and precise control.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Step 4: Start with One Tin</strong></p>
    <p>Never bulk-buy. Your preference will shift as you find your rhythm. Buy a single tin, use for a week, then decide if you want more or prefer to switch.</p>

