    <h2>FAQ: Your Top Nicotine Pouch Questions Answered</h2>

    <h3>What strength nicotine pouch should I start with?</h3>
    <p>If you're new to nicotine pouches, start with 3–6 mg/pouch. This delivers a light buzz without overwhelming effects. VELO Simply Spearmint Mini at 4 mg is specifically designed for beginners — the small format makes it easy to control duration and intensity.</p>

    <h3>Are stronger nicotine pouches safer than smoking?</h3>
    <p>Nicotine pouches are fundamentally different from smoking because they don't involve combustion. Even high-strength pouches like Siberia (33 mg/g) pose no smoke-related risks. However, very high strength is habit-forming and not recommended for casual users. Start with moderate strength and increase only if you're a regular user.</p>

    <h3>How long does a nicotine pouch last?</h3>
    <p>Most nicotine pouches release their nicotine over 30–60 minutes. Slim formats tend to last slightly shorter. You can control duration by removing the pouch early. For all-day use, one pouch every 1–2 hours is typical among regular users.</p>

    <h3>What's the difference between ZYN and VELO?</h3>
    <p>ZYN (owned by Swedish Match) is the world's leading brand, known for consistency and extreme availability. VELO (owned by BAT) offers more variety — 50+ products including zero-nicotine options — and tends toward innovative flavours. Both are high-quality; choice depends on whether you prioritise simplicity (ZYN) or variety (VELO).</p>

    <h3>Can I use nicotine pouches if I'm pregnant?</h3>
    <p>Nicotine is harmful to foetal development. You should not use any nicotine product — pouches, cigarettes, or vaping — during pregnancy. If you're trying to quit nicotine, speak with a healthcare provider about evidence-based cessation support.</p>

    <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

    <p>The nicotine pouch market is crowded, but quality is increasingly concentrated in a handful of proven leaders. If you want consistency and availability, ZYN Cool Mint wins. If you're exploring, VELO's breadth is unmatched. If you want refined quality, Kelly White and Skruf deliver.</p>

    <p>The "best" pouch is the one you reach for daily. Use our category winners as a starting point, commit to a tin, and adjust from there. Most users settle into one or two trusted brands within weeks.</p>

